    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 1995 Mazda RX-7 FD is a superlative example of rotary engineering, featuring the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW power plant. The engine exhibits exceptional compression across all rotor faces, ensuring optimal combustion cycle efficiency. The chassis retains its factory-spec torsional rigidity, complemented by the original double-wishbone suspension and a precise 50/50 weight distribution. Power is managed via a crisp five-speed manual transmission and delivered through a Torsen limited-slip differential. Every component, from the complex vacuum solenoid rack to the oil metering pump, has been preserved in factory-original condition. The exterior finish shows no signs of oxidation or clear-coat failure, while the interior remains free of the typical UV-induced dash delamination or bolster fatigue. A true turnkey specimen for the discerning enthusiast.",
